solution:
By Bayes' theorem
$$

P(V \mid D) = \frac{P(D \mid V)\,P(V)}{P(D \mid V) P(V) + P(D \mid V^c) P(V^c)}
= \frac{0.3 \cdot 0.6}{0.3 \cdot 0.6 + 0.5 \cdot 0.4}
= \frac{0.18}{0.38}
= \frac{9}{19} \approx 0.474.

$$
